Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_metric(25.10)                                            set_metric(25.10)

Name
       set_metric - Sets any defined metric to a value

Syntax
       set_metric

       -name <metric_name>

       -help

       -value <metric_value>

       Sets any defined metric to a value.

Parameters
       -name <metric_name >
              Specifies the name of the metric.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each set_metric parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man set_metric

       -value <metric_value>
              Specifies the value of the metric.

              Data_type: string, required

Examples
       The following command sets the value .base_cell.name ==  HDR*   to  the
       metric design.switch_cells.

       innovus  1>  set_metric  -name  design.switch_cells  [get_db  insts -if
       {.base_cell.name == HDR*}]

